reply_text:
@oratank yes, respectful to the source material. Changes ≠ disrespect. Lord of the Rings made several extremely major changes, but it was fine because it retained the spirit of the source material. The Invincible show is also receiving a number of changes from the original creator of the comic, because he wants to refine and improve his story.

Castlevania is wildly successful and receives tons of praise from critics and fans alike despite the changes you hate because it retains the spirit of the games, and even received a sequel spinoff.

Don’t get me wrong- the DMC anime could easily suck, but thinking it’s going to suck because of snippets of a scene revolving around a character never seen outside of an obscure prequel manga that most casual fans never even knew existed is absolutely ridiculous.

