@Spino-hx2mr  Compassion is what separates man from devil. True power is derived from "fighting like Hell to protect what matters", as Dante put it. Vergil, on the other hand, has nothing he cares about, nothing to protect. Even with the fruit of the Qliphoth, Vergil couldn't attain the "true power" he was seeking because Demons simply do not have the capacity to achieve such power.

Lady, a pure human, has feats that go far beyond what a normal human is capable of. And what set her on the path to achieving such power? Revenge. What spurred her desire for revenge? Love for her mother. Without love, there is no power. With love, even a human can surpass the strength of a demon.

Additionally, compassion itself doesn't curb your fear of Hell. I was rebuking his point that humans ONLY do good out of fear of Hell.

